default2.6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGovernance is changing in the city regions with most areas adopting the Co
defaultmbined Authority model to which
default PTEs will become either part of, or responsible to (the arrangements will vary in different areas). However, the pri
defaultnciple holds that the strategic planning and oversight of transport in complex conurbations is best done at the city region level. PTEs (for simplicity we will describe PTEs and any successor bodies as PTEs) have the 
defaultscale and capacity to assess and prioridefaulttise local transport schemes in a way that meets clear criteria as well as democratic oversightdefault. A recent report for 
defaultptegdefault by JMP sets out how this is done in more detail
default.
default2.7.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe 
defaultoptimum bodydefault depends on local circumstances (especially given the complex politi
defaultcal, economic and transport geography of England outside London) however for strategic 
defaulttransport decisions 
default(though not necessarily for all local transport decisions) it should be a reasonable fit with journey to work patterns and with functional local 
defaulteconomies. It should have adequate capacity to be able to carry out its planning and oversight functions in an efficient and professional way and it should also have a clear element of democratic oversight. We believe that for the city regions
default,
default in the evol
defaultving role of the PTEs, these criteria have
default,
default and will be
default,
default met. 
default2.8.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
